The latest stats from NetMarketShare show that Windows 10 is still behind Windows 7 on desktop, but it is catching up. The February 2018 statistics also revealed that iOS 11.2 and Android 7. 0 are the most popular mobile operating systems, with 21.26% and 20.91% market share respectively. Android 6.0 follows Android 7.0, with a market share of 17.22%. The most popular operating systems on desktop and mobile for February 2018 are detailed below.  